caption: I ordered an almond croissant 🥐 & (dark) baguette 🥖 to take home. Was authentic French baking. Was good.
great backyard area and nice wine selection
The best bread in Brooklyn!
Hands down greatest vegan chocolate chip cookies in existence. Actually best that I've tried, because I've not seen every vccc in existence. Bless these people and this place.
Amazing bread and pastries! Friendly staff
This place has excellent homemade bread. You really can't get better than this spot. They often sell out on certain loaves by afternoon. So, go early!

I had an appoint near by and the nurse told me about this place and how good their croissants were and she was not kidding. I got the almond croissant and a cappuccino. The cappuccino was really nice, it was the proper size and even with no added sugar it wasn't overly bitter or acidic. You can tell they defiently use fresh, good quality coffee. The croissant though is what will get me to return in the future. It was incredible, super buttery and flakey, sliced in half it was filled with a sweet and delicious almond filling and topped with a baked meringue for a bit of added sweetness and texture. When I say its the best croissant Ive ever had I mean it, I can't wait for my next appointment so I can try a different flavor, there are so many to choose from. I'd highly recommend supporting this local shop over one of the big chains. I spent about $10 which is what I anticipate to pay for a cappuccino and baked good just about anywhere but here it's defiently worth it. 😋

My favorite bread ever and the best almond croissant of my life. Gus is the queen mutha of baking. The whole L'imprimerie team is so so good--one of those incredibly unique small businesses that can never be duplicated. We're lucky they work so hard and with such care. Love love love!
Its a good thing this is a 25 min drive from my apartment and not closer, or I’d be having vegan croissants and quiche every f’in day. This man’s a genius. Bow down.

I love this bakery! They are always friendly and the pastries and bread are amazing. My favorites are the mixed berry danish, almond croissant and baguette. The ambiance is super cute, especially the back patio. Fortunately I live a short walk away, but it is worth the trip wherever you’re coming from!
Never fails for delicious bread and pasteries.

We love this place because the espresso is perfectly made and the PASTRIES OH THE PASTRIES!!  8/8/20 Edit- just had the rhubarb chocolate croissant. Also they are taking COVID protocol very seriously. Be prepared to follow rules or “No pastry for YOU!”  2/23/21- Most delicious maple cinnamon late. Also, I got the bacon snd cheddar quiche. Upon my first bite I said, “This is everything a bacon, egg, and cheese wants to be. But it not!” So delicious!!
Best bread has ever happened to me. Thank you for existing 💕

Hands down my top bakery to go to for pastries and bread in NYC. The staff are always lovely, the pastries are always on point (the almond croissants, cinnamon rolls and salted chocolate chip cookies are my fav) and the interior is so inviting! I always say, if I die, I hope that the afterlife has an unlimited supply of pastries from Limprimerie ❤️
Great bread, great pastries, great folks!
Amazing baked goods and bread.  Quiche is a BIT overpriced though at $8 IMO.
Came for their famous cinammon rolls and I was not disappointed! They sell out early and fast for a reason.
Really good quiche and sourdough bread that i used to make some tuna melts!

Absolutely spectacular bakery selling some of the best bread we've had in NYC in a while. The crust on the miche was nothing short of spectacular and the pastries were also very good (though I do prefer Nick's bakery in East Williamsburg a tiny bit wrt pastries but it's close ;-)
Great little bakery. Definitely a little pricey but the quality is there for sure. Favorite item here is the cinnamon roll. Sooooo good!!
Fantastic French bakery I’ve had a fortune of visiting.   The best croissant I’ve had in the city.

We like a lot hanging out. Yesterday we  visited this delicious place which friends told us about. We had a beautiful evening there with excellent cooking and a courteous crew and an impressive cook. We put this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall definitely return soon. We warmly recommend.

Don't bother ordering ahead of time, the phone numbers don't work, you have to wait online anyway to let them know you're here. Then they get orders done for people that show up after you. It's great when you're in a rush. I've been going here every Sunday for almost a year and call ahead of time and it's usually some issue or another. Pretty pricy for what it is, but sadly, it's the only decent worth while place for breakfast in the area. Pretty bad customer service! The guy literally said to me when I complained, "I really don't know what to tell you." You can start by apologizing. It's simple customer service 101.  If you like getting treated like dirt with even an apology, this is the place for you.
Love my burned black pastry for $5. Definitely will order again if they can burn them to ashes.
This is as close as you’re going to get to a Parisian patisserie in nyc! Try everything!
I worked for 6 months in an arisinal wood fired baker in France. The bread and pasteries at L'imprimerie is good as the best in the world.  We should all be grateful to have them as our neighbors.
Best bakery in Brooklyn, in my opinion
Very delicious sandwich, wasn't a huge fan of the bread, but the flavors were incredible. Would 100% be returning.
A nice spot in rundownarea with overpriced pastry.

that vegan chocolate chip cookie was honestly terrible soaked in oil etc. recipe needs a revamp. Ok went back and the black coffee has seriously gone downhill it was so sour and overpriced. Sticking to just buying the bread from now on
Destination spot. Worth coming to the neighborhood just for some pastries or sandwiches.
Best French bakery in Brooklyn !
Wow, you cannot go wrong with anything. I come here and get food for the whole day sometimes. We love Gus and his bakery! The lunch sandwiches are great and I love the tartines.
Best sandwiches ! They also sell pizza dough and sauce kits that are great for a socially distant pizza night!
Unbelievably beautiful breads and baked goods, a ton of which are vegan. Coffee is fantastic, as is the service - super friendly. Love stopping by here on a morning walk.
If you don’t get a Cinnamon Bun, you will die without having one of the greatest pastries ever made.

This is my favorite cheat-day spot and hands down the best French bakery in NYC. Everything is always fresh and delicious. It’s impossible to go there for one thing and not get tempted to buy more. Their croissants and bacon cheddar quiche are worth every calorie. As a plus the cold brew is always good and the staff is always friendly and helpful. Definitely a must visit if you’re in the area or in the mood for good French treats.

Go here for delicious pastries but skip the coffee, including espresso drinks. I've tried their iced coffee and latte (separate instances) and the coffee and shots tasted diluted. Today I ordered a small latte, it came with 2 shots and still tasted that way. Not sure why. So my 2 cents, go for the pastries and get your coffee elsewhere.

Incredible local French bakery with delicious pastries, breads, drinks, sandwiches, and more. The staff and owner are very friendly and care about their customers. They offer different levels of baked bread, if you prefer your bread on the lighter or darker side, which is awesome! I highly recommend getting their cinnamon rolls, croissants, quiches, Levain, baguettes, Miche, hot chocolate, and Danishes (and everything else they sell).
A rare find bakery. High quality breads.
Really good desserts, but their croissants are amazing!
Best chocolate chip cookies in Bushwick
So many vegan options and they’re REAL GOOD. And the bread is amazing. The people who work here are always friendly!

I’d throw someone into traffic for one of mama Gu’s baguettes. Every penny spent here was worth it, even the ones I shouldn’t have spent but did anyway. We lived down the street for six years, and since moving away life has become markedly less delicious.
Heaven on earth. Especially for vegans.

Best bakery around. Possibly in the city. Authentic french rustic breads and pastries. My favorites are the baguettes, olive bread, lemon cake and clafouti!  They also do nice danishes, croissants and cinammon rolls but it’s not necessarily the kind you’re accustomed to you uncouth Yankee.  Their instagram is worth following for the sass.  Make sure to order in advance because things like bread and cinnamon rolls sell out.
Gus, I love you.  Vickies scare me.
The have this almond and orange cake.. so freaking delicious!
Love the bread, love the sandwiches, love everything about this place.
Their sandwiches are to die for and their bread is delicious! We bought some and went home and made avocado toast and it was amazing. Highly recommend L’imprimerie!

Best boulangerie in NYC in my opinion. Delicious breads. Large selection of both vegan and non vegan pastries. Worth stopping regardless of whether you live in Bushwick or elsewhere in New York City. You won't be disappointed.

Best bakery I’ve found in NYC. The sourdough is for real. Plenty of vegan options (I don’t know how they do it with the laminated doughs, but they are legit). Supporting the community with sourdough starter, pizza kits, locally sourced ingredients, and all without missing a day during the pandemic.
Freakin love this place!!!!
Got fire pastries and bread every time I've visited with great service, people that complain about food service during a pandemic deserve the guillotine.

I ordered $50 worth of cinnamon rolls and had a terrible experience. I ordered 10 of them for my family and no one wanted to eat them. I sold them on the fresh beautiful pastries for breakfast and it was a completely different experience than.  They were extremely moist, practically wet and because they were package terribly picked into one tiny box squashed on top of each other almost half were breaking apart. They also don’t taste as fresh dough wise, although they said they were baked at 6 am. Most of them were also over baked with black/burnt spots. The burnt spots weren’t from the cinnamon but from rather being over baked. They use to be golden brown with bone white frosting and very crisp. When I opened the box I thought they were day old because of how they look, smell, taste.  I used to order from this bakery almost every weekend when I lived in Bushwick, this time I had a car pick them up because I am no longer in the area and wanted to support the business but this was not the experience I’m used to. They did refund the small cinnamon roll but it should not have been sent in the first place as it looked half eaten.  Update to owners response below: Adding an additional review because after the terrible experience the owner/worker is replying with no empathy, care or proper customer service. From his nasty reply you can clearly see his character. My review was 100% accurate of what I personally experienced. I am not trying to hurt anyone's business but share my experience with this bakery which I have every right to do. To add smart remarks such as maybe you uber driver ate, would be a fault on your part for not properly sealing or tapping the box, especially during covid. I was not trying to get any freebies as the money was already spent and I expected more for a $6 per cinnamon roll. Please see the bakeries response to see if this is the type of customer service you wish to experience after having a beyond disappointing experience. I was also harassed by email for my review.

I had the latte with honey and oat milk - it was amazing! Yes, it’s not cheap and yes, the cup is tiny but it was well worth it. The Honey Latte with almond milk at SBUX was my favorite before this but this is so much better. This drink is now my treat to myself. The sausage roll is also very tasty!

The best bakery in NYC! Service is so friendly! The cinnamon rolls , the bread, the pastries, the sandos! All so delicious I dream about them every week!! My husband is allergic to dairy so he had his FIRST EVER croissant here (vegan options!!) and it was PHENOM!  Thank you L'imprimerie !!
Best cinnamon rolls ever. This is my favorite bakery in NYC and definitely helped me survive quarantine.

This is the hands down the best bakery in nyc. Impeccable service, social justice undertones, and a commitment to serving the community during COVID (with safety protocols). Everything is beyond fresh and you will want to order it all - make sure to include the crousti. The negative reviewers don't understand that top notch ingredients make prices higher than your industrial plastic wrapped 99 cent baguette ...

This place reminded me of “Legay Choc” in Le Marais in Paris. The only difference is that their pastries are way overpriced. Very good but overpriced. $7.50 for a cake slice is beyond unreasonable, even in Brooklyn (especially that part of Brooklyn, which is far from being fancy). For good pastries at a better price try “Saraghina” in Bedford-Stuyvesant (on top of that you’ll hangout in a way more beautiful neighborhood full of brownstones on tree line streets). The place tastes more like Italy than France but you’ll love it. Nice try “L’imprimerie”.
Amazing, delicious breads. Friendly staff.
Very good coffee and pastries 😍 , chill back yard
Delicious bread, pastries, and sundries from the most handsome bearded French baker daddy around

L’imprimerie is by far the best bakery in New York. I’m always so impressed by the quality of their bread and pastries. There is clearly a lot of care, dedication and technical skill that goes into what they make everyday. Making great bread is hard work and a labor of love. That shines through from the owner, who is often personally at the bakery and greets each customer with a huge smile.  The staff are always lovely, recognize my husband and I each time we visit. That is the kind of customer service that is often hard to find in a big city.  I highly recommend their baguettes, chocolate chip cookies and any of their sourdough breads - particularly La Moisson.  I fully recognize that so many small businesses have been impacted by the current circumstances and I want L’imprimerie to know how much we appreciate what they do.

Favorite bakery in Bushwick... actually in all of NY.  Everything they sell is amazing from the breads to the tartines to the clafoutis to the cold brew. You will not be disappointed! If you visit on the weekend, get the olive sourdough (Marseillias) 😍🤤

Always the best bread and Gus never forgets the vegans! The Le crousti Is the best sweet thing i have ever eaten! And the cookie dough is so delicious! Recently they, added sandwiches to the menu and i legit crave the Avocat sandwich  because the olive oil is so delicious. With such beautiful and friendly staff, This place is a bushwick staple that i love to keep coming back to
Best bread I EVER HAD. The only birthday present I wanted was THIS BREAD. I hope I can eat it FOREVER  FOREVER!!!

Everything that I've had here has been amazing (croissants, cinnamon rolls, cookies, quiche, bread, pizza etc). What people don't seem to understand is that price reflects quality - you get what you pay for here. There's a Starbucks right down the street if you prefer your croissants from a vacuumed sealed plastic bag. They've stayed open serving the community during the entirety of Covid, changing their operation to be able to continue to open. They even gave out free sourdough starter so you could make your own at home.
(Translated by Google) Bread is good but not worth the price / value  (Original) El pan es bueno pero no vale la relación precio / valor
Their cinnamon rolls are so good. I think they only have them on the weekends though.

All the pastries and breads are baked fresh on site.  The croissant was fantastic, and the baguettes looked equally delicious. There's ample seating inside and a cozy, charming backyard patio.  They serve sandwiches and quiches in addition to the bakery items. The cappuccino was excellent.
Best pastries in nYc
One of the best bakeries in the city. A bold experimenter with flavors and combinations in traditional French bakery products.

Love everything about this place.  From the owner leaving his corporate life and reinventing himself into a master baker to their general ethos and social consciousness.  Doesn’t hurt that the breads and patisseries are perfection. My favorite is their seasonal clafoutis. Summer bliss. PS: For the self-entitled A**holes who think the right thing to do is to give a small business a 1 star review in the middle of a pandemic over an escargot pistache or a little extra wait, you’re the problem.
I got pistachio escargot for 5$ it was over baked and dry , no pistachio cream I don’t know why you call it pistachio . Pistachio powder on top is not enough to call it Like that .
Excellent baked good.  So many delicious varieties of bread you'll lose your mind.

I love this bakery--it's been a real source of comfort during the COVID-19 pandemic. Their breads are unbelievably delicious. Cinnamon buns? Best I've ever had. There are so many different treats to try here. I love it. Go go go and support this local business!
It's really good, they're really nice here. I haven't been before and they were really patient explaining what they had. The foods really good to I had the millionaire bar and it's so good.
The smell of this shop is amazing! The bread and cakes are super delicious! They have also been selling sour dough starter, pizza kits, and yeast during the pause, which has been great.
Over priced. Not too impressed with pistachio escargot & the baguette. Haven't tried the miche
Delicious! Croissant was soooo good, gone before I made photo. Employee was friendly and helpful. Thank you! Definitely will come back
Expensive but super great coffee and the the bread is out of this world.

This place is amazing. They have the social distancing guidelines down. The baked goods are out of this world. They also have a pizza kit for essential workers for free which is super kind <3 I am so grateful to have this in the neighborhood.

Gus makes the best bread and baked goods. BK is lucky to have a artisan bakery like this! Always a joy to visit. Try the chocolate croissants! Buy some sourdough for dinner! We make sure to visit when we are in town
I was craving a loaf of bread for the soup I made and they had beautiful bread, it made my soup come together. Props to the bakers, I'll be coming back soon
Definitely not a French bakery..  no brioche available
Killer croissants, cute little cafe. People working there are nice.
amazing quiche 😭

Love the bread from this place. It’s a family favorite. When we can’t make it to this location it is the bread carried by other local businesses in Bushwick. I love their vegan pastries and the call out of the vegan bread types.
The Moisson loaf is the best loaf of bread I've ever had!
The food is always fresh and yummy, staff members gives good customer service. I love the cleanliness and ambience. Will come visit again.
Best bread, cutest baristas
Best cinnamon rolls,spacious space, friendly staff
Best bread and pastries in Bushwick
Amazing pastries and great coffee. Good atmosphere, friendly service, and plenty of sockets to charge your phone. As a passing traveller I didn't try any of the breads but they also looked amazing.
Best cinnamon buns in Brooklyn
Café with nice bakery
Best ice tea and croissant. People who work there are great too! So thankful I found this little gem of a place.
Couldn't get enough! Everything we got was amazing. So yummy!!
Fantastic, unbelievable sourdough bread and pastries. It’s practically good for you!
Take a bite, close your eyes and you'll swear you've flown to Paris. A+ pastries.

I'd have never know about this place except for a mention in a YouTube video! The pastries were worth the journey from Astoria to Brooklyn: flakey, buttery but light, with just enough sweetness. Looking forward to trying the sourdough bread and baguette next.
Cutest little bakery with amazing fresh cakes and good coffee (latte not filter)

Not only was I impressed with the range of baked goods that I tried, but the service was outstanding. Patient with questions and a lovely manner, Perry was engaging and knowledgeable. Just delighted that I was there early and didn't have to rush. The lemon pistachio bar was especially good, as was the chocolate chip cookie and multigrain loaf of bread. Superb!
Love heading here on a weekend morning. Delicious, buttery, delicate yet decadent pastries. The breads stand out on their own. All of great quality.
I always get an iced latte with oat milk that is delicious and creamy. Today was my first time getting anything edible and oh my goodness!! Go here! I got the cacahuete. You're welcome.

(Translated by Google) Best bakery in Bushwick, if not Brooklyn. Their Bread The Harvest is just crazy - I can not live without it.  (Original) Meilleure boulangerie de Bushwick, si ce n’est de Brooklyn. Leur pain La Moisson est juste dingue - je ne peux pas m’en passer.
best bread bakery around. The parmesan with cracked pepper leaves and the raisin and walnut loaves are great. I need to work my way through all of the rest.
Pricey but quality French pastries.

Delicious taste, something I feel like gets overlooked with bread. I feel like we Americans seek out texture in all that we eat, to the point where some bake shops taste crispy but not proofed... I don't know if that makes sense, but regardless I enjoyed the flavor of the pastry here! My photo is garbage, but I wanted to show that they got some good stuff going on. Spectrum Coffee is really good too!
The bread is soooo good!
This place has the best French pastries has down in Brooklyn and good coffee.
Everything a croissant should be One small suggestion, the dusty printing press is kind of gross and takes up a lot of otherwise useable space
Kind of pricey, but the food is good.

Hands down the best baguettes in NYC, compares to the ones I used to get in Paris. Too bad these ones aren't just €1... but to get this good of a baguette in NYC I guess ya gotta pay! Plus the pan au chocolate is fabulous, and I come here sometimes for their sourdough bread. Love living near a place that bakes things fresh.
Most legitimate French bakery! Sourdough! Baguettes! And also great coffee!
I tried this spot before with a friend and I am addicted since then. I enjoy the good character and delicious dishes and drinks. I recommend this place.
Amazing bagette and pastries. Great people.
Best croissants! A local gem.
Best almond croissant in the city!
Wonderful cafe with great pastries and cute back garden. Very European!!
Kind, cute staff and everything I've ever had from here has been delicious!
BEST BREAD IN BUSHWICK HANDS DOWN, a bit pricey but worth it

Bread is fresh and delicious. Located in an unassuming location near the Bushwick/Ridgewood border, so it has a very nice neighborhood feel. Queer friendly business, they serve excellent coffee. A tartine and coffee for lunch can set you back over $20, but it’s worth it. Sit in the back yard!
Great bread, welcoming athmosphere. Highly recommend!
Over priced, comedically poor service, subpar food.  They’ll try to give you salads on the side of your sandwiches. Be warned they, they’re 10 bucks for a bunch of leaves flooded with vinaigrette.
Freshly baked breads and pastries daily.
Excellent sour dough but very expensive compared against what you get in the UK

Cute bakery with great baguettes. I'm picky about baguettes, but these were the perfect balance between soft and crispy. Coffee and pastries available as well. Get the almond croissant! You won't be disappointed.

Nice coffee shop with delicious tartines and viennoiseries proposed by a French baker. We were welcomed by a friendly young man who spoke very good french and helped us with our command. Very expensive and long wait but worth it
Good cranberry/ Raisin Bread

Nice French bakery/cafe in Bushwick. The almond croissant has some meringue on top. It is flaky outside and buttery/airy inside. Clear layers with a perfect amount of almond paste. The paste is a little bit liquid though.
Amazing baguettes
All of the breads are great. Pastries are great. Millionaires are delicious. Haven't been disappointed by anything there.
Almond Croissants make you fat but taste so good
Tears of joy biting into their cinnamon roll. Good lord!
Food is great. Patio is great. Waiting time is toooo long.  And my order was forgotten.
One of my favorite places - some of the best bread in Brooklyn!
Delectable orange-almond cake. Their bread also looks fabulous.

By far the best croissants in the five boroughs. Everything from the classic butter to the mind blowing chocolate almond with toasted meringue on top is so good even on a rainy day which a lot of chefs struggle with. Their coffee could be better but that's not why I go. Great Sunday ritual.
Pastry perfection. Great spot to sit and enjoy or grab and go
Best fresh bread, croissants and coffee ever!
Excellent coffee, croissants, and cakes. Very friendly staff. Great location just steps away from the L train.
Best Croissant ever
Great pastries and coffee. Staff is nice, too!

Very cute place in a part of BK rhat I'm note sure is ready for it yet. The pastries are not notch nothing overly sweet. Great chocolate croissants, an amazing oranage, almond flour (GF) cake and solid c.c cookies. Thad a wide array of fresh baked breads. Although I wasnt in need for break then, they looked amazing.

Great spacious neighborhood bakery with beautifully baked and delicious baked goods including an assortment of croissants, danishes quick breads, cookies, as well as various country loaves. There's definitely something for everyone. Coffee is also perfectly prepared.
Sourdoughs are great, service is great, iced teas are yummy. Pretty dang tasty all around. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Passing by
A bit too pricy for the breakfast delights
Tasty baked goods, friendly staff.
Fantastic coffee and exceptional pastry/breads

This is a fantastic little bakery, with superb coffee, pastries and a wonderful owner, Gus. There are the classic pastries as well as some savory items like quiches and fun croissants like chocolate and jalapeno or the sausage croissant.

Easily the best bread in Bushwick / possibly New York City. I bring people the cereal bread all the time...and I definitely might have destroyed entire baguettes on my walk home.  Left the bakery one day at the same time as the owner, Gus. Talked with him for several blocks, thanking him for bringing such a great bakery to our neighborhood. Seems like a super nice dude, and his love for his craft is immediately apparent with the first bite of any of the breads. Would recommend even to people I hate.

This perfect bakery is a gem in the area. Whether to study, start your day, enjoy a quick bit or all at once this is the place.  It starts with amazing fresh made breads and pastries. In particular is the weekend only Black Peppercorn Parmesan that is worth a trip every weekend.  Staff is fun and polite and the seating is surprisingly spacious with a summer time outside area to escape the bustling track above.  If you live in the area or live of the L, J or M, L'imprimerie is worth the trip.  My only minor extremely nitpicky complaint is their insufferable glass coffee mugs that are too small and you end up burning your finger before you can even burn your mouth! But this probably says more about me than them.
Very good coffee
Extremely good bread and croissants. Always swear it off due to the fact that  but in the end I come back because the croissants are that good, even though they are over $4 and small.
Relaxed place, great bread and coffee
Dope coffee and some of the best pastries in BK
everything you try here will be amazing.

I love this bakery! Their baked goods are amazing!! It was highly recommended to me by another amazing bakery, Babettes. I had an almond cake that was moist and covered in an orange simple syrup. It was a very high note to end my vacation on. The coffee was also delicious! A great paring of delicious pastries and coffee.
Try latte with oat milk!!
I don’t hate it
Great bread, and Gus is hot
Friendly and tasty
Delicious croissants!
Good pain au chocolat but didn't like paying for the butter and jelly - seemed over the top for such a small amount..
The bread is so so good! But the toast in the cafe is kinda expensive and when we got the croissants they came cold. Wish they had heated it back up.
Best chocolate croissants I’ve had since Europe and overall my favorite cafe in nyc

Although I did not try the baked delectables they looked out of this world. The coffee was strong and no nonsense. This is clearly a locals place that stands out for its French vibe amidst a neighborhood of Latin, Cuban, and Mexican influences. There are two nice tables for hanging out and some bar seats in front of both windows.

To borrow from Teen vogue, I saw Sailor Socialism’s aka Dasha’s podcast’s co-host here and she did not acknowledge me when I said I liked red scare. Nice place for a fancy coffee underneath a railroad. I ate the Bread and didn’t realize it was something until i saw the hype
Good but way overpriced.
Honestly the best bakery I have ever been to, this is the one spot I ALWAYS get seconds. Great employees, great owner, great food. I cried when I first ate here.
Worthwhile making the trip from Manhattan! The  best French bakery in all 5 boroughs.
Best bread in all of NYC
Best baguette in NYC!!!
delicious Mimosa 👌
Really good!!

This place lives up to the hype! I got a chocolat amandes croissant, a cinnamon roll, and a loaf of miche. The cinnamon roll was ridiculously good — laminated like a croissant, with loads of butter and sugar that caramelized into crispy edges. People are right in that it’s pricier than other bakeries, but it’s also the best pastry I’ve had in Brooklyn in ages. You must go!
Really nice bread (loafs and baguette) pastries and coffee. They have oatly milk and vegan food options. Honestly the best bread in a large area by far.

Quite pricey but extremely tasty and high quality food! Had an avocado bread with a mixed salad. I also enjoyed the atmosphere. They even had a little cosy backyard area outside. Another plus was their clean and well designed toilet :-)
Incredibly delicious and high quality!
Wonderful Espresso and the best loaves of bread in NYC
An outstanding French bakery. Go here! Best croissant I've ever had
Best baked goods I've had outside of Paris.
Cute little place. The back patio is where the magic happens.
The employees were so friendly, the quiche was delicious, and the tea was delightful. I'll be back soon!
Cereal bread + a picnic blanket at a park = Total fun
Delicious mushroom feta danish and a Millionaire dessert that is a sweet tooth’s dream -magnifiqué!
I want to like this place but it's absurdly overpriced and I've had much better pastries and croissants for less even in Manhattan.
Amazing pastry and coffee!

Amazing pastries is enough of a reason to visit but their coffee, sandwich, and bread selections are amazing as well. I spent over 20 here because I had to try multiple things and I had no regret. The staff is helpful and friendly and made the experience that much better. Unfortunately for my waistline, I don't think I could go a week with out one of their pastries.
L’imprimerie rules! Pastries are excellent and a great place to work. It’s nice and quiet, with good music.
They're pastry is delicious and their staff is friendly. What more can you ask for? Great coffee? Ah they got you there too. 🤭

Yes it's a little pricey for the neighborhood but Gus really really really knows how to bake. He is the real French pastry chef deal. The love and care into every loaf, pastry and quiche can be tasted. Good for a treat, or pick up a loaf and bring it home!
Great Coffee if you like fruity notes of peach. friendly cozy place.
Because I've lived in France I can say that this is about the perfect French bakery in New York

A bushwick gem with a sinful selection of sweet and selection of sweet and savory pastries. If you go on a weekend, try their speciality cinnamon bun. Seating options more limited in winter, so make sure to go back for their hidden backyard when the sun comes out.
Incredible goodness! Tasty and creative choices!

Cozy, retro vibe at this french bakery / bistro?  new addition in the middle of working class  Buswick catering to  young urban yuppies as prices are clearly out of reach to working class dwellers (majority). I enjoyed lunch and a nice cafe. Menu entrees were in French !

I got two baguettes. The one with the sections was burnt and falling apart on one side. Both baguettes tasted ok but seemed to be lacking with the flavor. Maybe something with the fermentation. Shape and texture looked ok.
One of the best places in this neighborhood. Cinnamon rolls, cookies, and almond croissant are all amazing. But the real secret is pizza Sundays. Low key best pizza around, don’t @ me.

What a pleasure to have such a high quality bakery in the neighborhood. The salted chocolate chip cookie is arguably one of the best I've ever had. It's simple, but basically perfect! The breads and pastries are all top notch. if you're in Bushwick and haven't tried it, you're missing out.

I live around the corner from this place. I stop by every 3 or 4 months when I'm feeling homesick and want a pain au chocolat for breakfast. Unfortunately I always leave disappointed. First up, it's waaaay too expensive. I know that the market drives the prices and that I can't expect french bakery prices in Brooklyn. I actually wouldn't mind paying $4 for the pain au chocolat if it was excellent, but it's not. It's burnt and chewy. Like everything in this bakery it's overcooked. I guess that's how the baker likes his bread, and that's perfectly fine. But any decent bakery should offer their bread and pastries between "blanc" (white, slightly undercooked) and "brun" (brown, slightly overcooked). Here you can have any shade that you want, as long as it's dark brown. :D  The rest of their food (quiches, cakes, tartes…) is legitimately good though.
Amazing bread selection... I want to try them all!

Excellent thin and crusty baguette. The croissant and pain au chocolat are also some of the best I’ve tasted in NYC so far. They have a nice variety of quiche as well. I tried the tomato, basil and mozzarella which was delicious.

All the pastries and breads are baked fresh on site.  The croissant was fantastic, and the baguettes looked equally delicious. There's ample seating inside and a cozy, charming backyard patio.  They serve sandwiches and quiches in addition to the bakery items. The cappuccino was excellent.

I come here a couple times a week specifically for their quiche! Sooo good! I'm obsessed with tomato mozarella one. I love the interior of the place and the small back yard area is super cute. The staff is very friendly. Definitely one of my favourite places in the neighborhood.

Not an imitator, this place is a legitimate bakery with the talent to back it up. Tried the chocolate chip cookie, cinnamon bun and pain au chocolat. Incredibly good. Excellent coffee!

I like this shop.  I was passing through the northern leg of Brooklyn, in search of some good coffee to go with my lunch -- when, suddenly, I stumbled upon this nifty, low-key cafe. Talk about serendipity. A friendly barista took my order, and just like that, I'm lunching and sipping and reading on a comfy bench, watching Myrtle Avenue scroll by like real-life TV. Hooray! Even after I was finished, the shop had another treat in store for me, in the form of the most charming little bathroom I've ever used in my life. If I ever find myself in this neck of the woods again, I'll probably return to L'imprimerie.  My thanks goes out to all associated with this business. I am grateful for, and have benefited from, your work and service. Keep it up, ladies and gents!
Cool coffee shop - Just what we were looking for. And free refills :)

(Translated by Google) Despite the decent products offered by a French baker, the prices are exorbitant. $ 4 for an overcooked chocolate bun or $ 3 for a croissant too overcooked. I advise all French homesick to go for breakfast at this address.  (Original) Malgré les produits convenables proposés par un boulanger français, les prix sont exorbitants. 4$ pour un pain au chocolat trop cuit ou bien 3$50 pour un croissant lui aussi trop cuit. Je déconseille à tous français en mal du pays d'aller prendre un petit dejeuner à cette adresse.

It's 7am. Time for work. You push your boy toy's arm off of you, the one your wife doesn't know about yet, eagerly getting dressed to the dismay of your... well, you don't want to label it.  "I have to go to work." A lie. Lying to your booty call? A new low. If only they knew. Maybe it's time that they knew you make excuses to go to L'imprimerie. Maybe it's time they knew that it wasn't Miguel that you longed for -- that Gus, the baker, with his big bushy beard and dough-covered Crocs, is really your 'other man'. 😛  His laugh. His smile. His pink socks. If only he knew how good his sticky, sweet frosting was on those cinnamon-smothered buns -- or how exciting it was to bite into his crispy, double-baked almond croissants to find an explosion of nutty almond paste inside, underneath a beard of almond mousse.  If my wife knew about this place, it would make her jealous.
